fields.title: Python Interview
fields.description: Interview focusing on Python fundamentals and advanced concepts.

fields.title: Django Interview
fields.description: Interview focusing on Django framework, ORM, and architecture.

fields.title: PostgreSQL Interview
fields.description: Interview focusing on PostgreSQL database concepts and performance.

fields.question: What are Python's key features?
fields.answer: Python is interpreted, dynamically typed, and supports multiple paradigms including OOP and functional programming.

fields.question: Explain Python's GIL.
fields.answer: The Global Interpreter Lock ensures only one thread executes Python bytecode at a time.

fields.question: Difference between list and tuple?
fields.answer: Lists are mutable while tuples are immutable.

fields.question: How do Python decorators work?
fields.answer: Decorators wrap a function, modifying its behavior without changing its code.

fields.question: What is list comprehension?
fields.answer: A concise syntax to create lists using a single line of code.

fields.question: What are Django signals?
fields.answer: Signals let decoupled apps receive notifications when certain actions occur.

fields.question: How does Django ORM work?
fields.answer: It translates Python class models into SQL queries behind the scenes.

fields.question: What are Django middlewares?
fields.answer: They are hooks that process requests and responses globally.

fields.question: How do you implement custom user models in Django?
fields.answer: By extending AbstractBaseUser or AbstractUser and updating AUTH_USER_MODEL.

fields.question: What are PostgreSQL’s key features?
fields.answer: It supports advanced indexing, JSONB, CTEs, and transactional DDL.

fields.question: Explain VACUUM in PostgreSQL.
fields.answer: VACUUM reclaims storage occupied by dead tuples and updates statistics.

fields.question: What are indexes in PostgreSQL?
fields.answer: Indexes improve query performance by speeding up lookups.

fields.question: How do transactions work in PostgreSQL?
fields.answer: Transactions group multiple queries into a single atomic operation.

fields.question: What is the difference between INNER JOIN and LEFT JOIN?
fields.answer: INNER JOIN returns only matching rows, LEFT JOIN returns all from left table plus matches.
